  {
    "id": "f_csv_89cf5eec69",
    "slug": "the-argument-is-made-that-naming-god-is-never-really-naming-god-but-only-naming",
    "texto": "The argument is made that naming God is never really naming God but only naming our understanding of God. To take our ideas of the divine and hold them as if they correspond to the reality of God is thus to construct a conceptual idol built from the materials of our mind.",
